      Subclasses of AlgorithmComponent in io.smudgr.extensions.image.alg.bound 
      Modifier and Type Class and Description
      class  Bound
      The Bound class is an AlgorithmComponent that defines behavior for restricting the focus of an Algorithm to a parameterized rectangle.
      class  EllipticalBound
      The EllipticalBound implementation of Bound represents a parameterized ellipse to bind an Algorithm to

    • Uses of AlgorithmComponent in io.smudgr.extensions.image.alg.coord

      Subclasses of AlgorithmComponent in io.smudgr.extensions.image.alg.coord 
      Modifier and Type Class and Description
      class  ConvergeCoords
      The ConvergeCoords coordinate function generates coordinate sets that angle inward to a configurable center.
      class  CoordFunction
      The abstract CoordFunction is an AlgorithmComponent that specifies in what order an Operation should act on the PixelFrame.
      class  RadialCoords
      The RadialCoords coordinate function generates coordinates that resemble a spiral.
      class  SkewedCoords
      The SkewedCoords coordinate function generates coordinates that are parallel to each to each other at a constant parameterized angle.
      class  StraightCoords
      The StraightCoords coordinate function simply creates a coordinate set in a column direction.

    • Uses of AlgorithmComponent in io.smudgr.extensions.image.alg.op

      Subclasses of AlgorithmComponent in io.smudgr.extensions.image.alg.op 
      Modifier and Type Class and Description
      class  ChannelBleed
      Channel Bleed rotates colors using a bitwise function for a weird digi-acid effect.
      class  ChannelCrush
      Channel Crush uses a configurable bitwise function to squash RGB layer information, resulting in a image with a singular color palette and bolder forms, at the price of texture detail.
      class  ChannelDrift
      Channel Drift shifts image RGB layers separately by parameterized amounts.
      class  ChannelSort
      ChannelSort sorts pixels but on a masked portion of the pixel.
      class  DataBend
      Data Bend mimics the popular Wordpad effect, with a configurable 'Target' byte to replace a set 'Amount' of times.
      class  HSVLModifier
      HSV/L Modifier provides a traditional manipulation for saturation, hue, and brightness.
      class  Marbeler
      Marbeler iteratively shifts pixel columns in alternating directions for a marble-esque distortion.
      class  Operation
      The Operation abstract class is an AlgorithmComponent that defines behavior for executing a pixel manipulation algorithm.
      class  ParallelOperation
      The abstract ParallelOperation class allows implementors to easily execute an operation in parallel across each pixel index list.
      class  ParticlePush
      Particle Push takes pixels and displaces them by a univariate scaled shift amount.
      class  PixelShift
      Pixel Shift simply shifts pixels by a given amount, within interval offsets, along the current Algorithm selected pixel sets.
      class  PixelSort
      Pixel Sort, as implied by its name, sorts pixels in forward or reverse order using the value of each pixel as calculated by a configurable function.
      class  RainbowBend
      I actually have no idea what this does.
      class  Smear
      I honestly haven't played with this so who knows
      class  SourceMixer
      Source Mixer allows the traditional blending of two images, one being the passed in PixelFrame and another being a configurable Source
      class  SpectralShift
      Spectral Shift buckets pixels using their value as calculated by a function, and replaces each pixel in that bucket with a distinct color.

    • Uses of AlgorithmComponent in io.smudgr.extensions.image.alg.select

      Subclasses of AlgorithmComponent in io.smudgr.extensions.image.alg.select 
      Modifier and Type Class and Description
      class  AllSelect
      The AllSelect class simply returns true for all pixels.
      class  EdgeSelect
      EdgeSelect attempts to only select pixels based on their proximity to an 'edge', or strong form in the image.
      class  RangeSelect
      RangeSelect selects pixels based on their value within a range of values, as calculated by a configurable function.
      class  Selector
      The abstract Selector class defines an AlgorithmComponent that uses actual pixel values of an image to focus an Operation.
